==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Morbidezza
<hw>Mor`bi*dez"za</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.,
softness, delicacy. See <er>Morbid</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Fine
Arts)</fld> <def>Delicacy or softness in the representation of
flesh.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A term used as a direction in
execution, signifying, with extreme delicacy.</def>
<rj><au>Ludden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Morbidity</ent>⟦br⟧
